  "source_notes": "A researcher quoted \"Tales From The Heart: True Stories of My Childhood\" Chapter 2 My Birth: \"At 1 in the afternoon...Two hours later I was born.\"\\n\\nSy Scholfield found the full quote: \"At one in the afternoon, rushing in from every outlying corner, the mas invaded La Pointe. When the first beats of the gwoka shook the pillars of heaven, as if she were waiting for that very signal, my mother lost her waters. My father, my brothers and sisters, and the servants went into a panic. No cause for alarm. Two hours later, I was born.\"\\nThe \"researcher\" gave the year as 1937 but no year is given in ''Tales From The Heart''. Scholfield changed the year to 1934 which is given in various biographical resources. \\n\\n",
